						<summary>

						<p>This might be an inscription of Kulōttuṅga II. It records the gift of a silver vessel with a golden nozzle (?), weighing about 104 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi>, for use in <hi rend="italic">abhishēka</hi> of the god Aṇḍanāyaka, by one Vēlveṭṭi Uyyakkoṇḍār-Bhaṭṭa Śrīvachchadēva-Bhaṭṭa. Tiruviśalūr is here said to be a part of Ediriliśōḻa-chaturvēdimaṅgalam an <hi rend="italic">agaram</hi> in Maṇṇi-nāḍu, a subdivision of Virudarājabhayaṅkara-vaḷanāḍu.</p>						

						</summary>
